<div class="doc-content">
  <h3>Color and the Palette</h3>
  <p>
    <code>ember-paper</code> uses the same color palettes and palette names as Angular Material and <a href="https://material.google.com/style/color.html">Material Design</a>. Each pallete contains 14 shades/tints of the specified hue for use by components in diffierent situations. The definitive shade/tint is <code>'500'</code>. Specify the desired palette(s) prior to importing <code>ember-paper.scss</code>.
  </p>
  {{code-snippet name="theme.import.scss"}}
  <h3>Overriding Variables</h3>
  <p>
    Many of the sass variables are defined with <code>!default</code>. This allows a variable to be overridden by a previous definition. Make overrides prior to importing the file defining the variable.
  </p>
  <p>
    You can modify the colors in the palette you are using for <code>$primary</code>, <code>$accent</code>, or <code>$warn</code>. You can also define an entirely new palette and specify it by a new name as the primary, accent, or warn color.
  </p>
  <h3>Using theme colors in your custom SASS</h3>
  <p>
    <code>ember-paper</code> provides the <code>color</code> sass function which looks-up the specified shade/tint from the specified palette and return the appropriate color.
  </p>
  {{code-snippet name="theme.color-function.scss"}}
